gw.plugin.contact

Interface ContactSystemPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface ContactSystemPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    Defines the contract for integration to an external contact system.

    • Method Detail

      • retrieveContact

        Contact retrieveContact(java.lang.String contactUId,
                        ContactCreator creator)
        Retrieve a contact from external system. If a Contact exists in PolicyCenter with the same AddressBookUID, that Contact will first be loaded, and then any fields retrieved from the external system overlaid. If the Contact does not exist in PolicyCenter, a new (uncommitted) Contact will be minted in the bundle provided by the creator, with values from the external system.
        Parameters:
        contactUId - the unique id of the contact in external system
        creator - the contact creator
        Returns:
        A populated Contact entity in the creator's bundle

      • searchContacts

        ContactResult[] searchContacts(ContactSearchCriteria searchCriteria)
        Search for matching contacts in external systems.
        Parameters:
        searchCriteria - the contact search criteria
        Returns:
        An array of ContactResults that contains the results of the search

      • supportsFindingDuplicates

        boolean supportsFindingDuplicates()
        Return true if the external system is capable of finding and returning duplicate contacts. If this method returns false, then a call to findDuplicates() may throw an exception, but in any event cannot be relied upon to return legitimate results.
        Returns:
        true if the External Contact System supports finding duplicates, false if not

      • findDuplicates

        DuplicateContactResultContainer findDuplicates(Contact contact)
        Finds duplicates for the contact in the external system.
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact to find potential duplicates for
        Returns:
        a duplicate result container that holds the actual results

      • addContact

        void addContact(Contact contact,
                java.lang.String transactionId)
         throws ContactCommunicationException
        Notifies an external contact system about the creation of a new contact. There may be side-effects on the contact, typically to store external identifiers.
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact that the external contact system is being notified about. There may be side-effects on this contact within this method which need to be clearly documented in implementing plugins.
        transactionId - uniquely identifies this operation, and reused for retries during communication errors
        Throws:
        ContactCommunicationException - if communication with the contact manager fails

      • addContact

        void addContact(Contact contact,
                java.lang.String payload,
                java.lang.String transactionId)
         throws ContactCommunicationException
        Notifies an external contact system about the creation of a new contact. There may be side-effects on the contact, typically to store external identifiers.
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact that the external contact system is being notified about. There may be side-effects on this contact within this method which need to be clearly documented in implementing plugins.
        payload - describe the contact for the external system and should be in whatever format the external system accepts (e.g. XML specified by a published XSD)
        transactionId - uniquely identifies this operation, and reused for retries during communication errors
        Throws:
        ContactCommunicationException - if communication with the contact manager fails

      • updateContact

        void updateContact(Contact contact,
                   java.lang.String changes,
                   java.lang.String transactionId)
            throws ContactCommunicationException
        Notifies an external contact system about changes to a contact. There may be side-effects on the contact, typically to store external identifiers.
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact that the external contact system is being notified about. There may be side-effects on this contact within this method which need to be clearly documented in implementing plugins.
        changes - describes the changes for the external system and should be in whatever format the external system accepts (e.g. XML specified by a published XSD)
        transactionId - uniquely identifies this operation, and reused for retries during communication errors
        Throws:
        ContactCommunicationException - if communication with the contact manager fails

      • overwriteContactWithLatestValues

        void overwriteContactWithLatestValues(Contact contact,
                                      java.lang.String addressBookUID)
        Overwrites the given contact with the latest values from the contact in the external system that has the given addressBookUID
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact that the external contact system is being notified about. There may be side-effects on this contact within this method which need to be clearly documented in implementing plugins.
        addressBookUID - the id of the contact in the external system whose fields should overwrite the fields of the given contact

      • removeContact

        void removeContact(Contact contact,
                   java.lang.String removeInfo,
                   java.lang.String transactionId)
            throws ContactCommunicationException
        Notifies an external contact system about the removal of a contact.
        Parameters:
        contact - the contact that the external contact system is being notified about.
        removeInfo - describes the contact via LinkID plus additional information such as updating user and app for the external system and should be in whatever format the external system accepts (e.g. XML specified by a published XSD)
        transactionId - uniquely identifies this operation, and reused for retries during communication errors
        Throws:
        ContactCommunicationException - if communication with the contact manager fails

      • getReplacementAddressABUID

        java.lang.String getReplacementAddressABUID(java.lang.String oldAddressABUID)
        Finds the replacement Address AddressBookUID for the given Address AddressBookUID. This is called when doing merges or updates where a PC critical address is removed by the Contact Management System - if there is a replacement address we will link to that Address instead; if there is no replacement, PolicyCenter will delink the Address from the CMS (null out the AddressBookUID) as we still depend on the Address.
        Parameters:
        oldAddressABUID - - the old Address ABUID to find a replacement for
        Returns:
        ABUID of the Address that replaced the old Address, or null if there is no replacement
